WEBVTT

00:03.033 --> 00:04.701
Hey.

00:04.701 --> 00:06.334
What you doing?

00:06.334 --> 00:08.801
Just sealing
some attic joists.

00:08.801 --> 00:10.100
Why would you have to seal stuff

00:10.100 --> 00:12.133
that's gonna be
inside the attic?

00:12.133 --> 00:14.901
You gonna have to seal me too
because I live up there?

00:14.901 --> 00:16.667
Roof changes temperature
all the time.

00:16.667 --> 00:18.100
Makes the wood
draw in moisture.

00:18.100 --> 00:19.701
You-- You don't want it
to rot, so...

00:19.701 --> 00:22.467
Where, um--?
Where are you going?

00:22.467 --> 00:24.133
I got some work upstairs.

00:24.133 --> 00:25.334
Sam, can you stop?

00:25.334 --> 00:26.801
Can we stop this, because

00:26.801 --> 00:28.667
it's kind of obvious
you're avoiding me.

00:28.667 --> 00:30.033
I'm not avoiding you.

00:30.033 --> 00:31.868
Every time I come near you,
it's--

00:31.868 --> 00:34.000
It's some new excuse as to why
you have to be at--

00:34.000 --> 00:35.901
I don't know at the opposite end
of the house.

00:35.901 --> 00:38.734
I'm just...

00:38.734 --> 00:40.267
I'm doing my job. Okay?

00:40.267 --> 00:42.834
Uh-huh. And so why are you
backing away from me?

00:42.834 --> 00:44.601
Because...

00:47.334 --> 00:48.834
I'm avoiding you, okay?

00:48.834 --> 00:50.701
Sam--

00:50.701 --> 00:53.000
Look, Julia, I'm sorry,
but th-this-- This thing

00:53.000 --> 00:58.334
that you think is happening, I
mean, us... whatever, it's not.

00:58.334 --> 01:00.100
Why not?

01:00.100 --> 01:01.701
Julia, give me a break.
You're 16.

01:01.701 --> 01:03.200
Seventeen.
And I'm 24

01:03.200 --> 01:05.667
and the whole thing, it just
doesn't make any-- Any sense.

01:05.667 --> 01:06.667
Why?

01:06.667 --> 01:07.734
No. I-- I mean, it.

01:07.734 --> 01:09.501
Give me one good reason.

01:09.501 --> 01:11.167
How about you're still
in high school,

01:11.167 --> 01:13.167
and it's practically illegal.

01:13.167 --> 01:16.234
Look-- Look, you can't--
You-- You can't vote.

01:16.234 --> 01:18.100
You-- You can't go into a bar.

01:18.100 --> 01:19.434
You can barely even drive.

01:19.434 --> 01:20.601
I said a good reason.

01:20.601 --> 01:22.834
Julia, please.
I mean, we kissed each other.

01:22.834 --> 01:24.434
No, no, no. You kissed me.

01:24.434 --> 01:26.734
And you kissed me back.
Don't deny it.

01:26.734 --> 01:28.133
I was there.
I'm not doing this.

01:28.133 --> 01:30.701
And we- We used to talk, like--
Like, all the time,

01:30.701 --> 01:33.267
and hang out with each other.
I mean, I'm not imagining this.

01:33.267 --> 01:35.033
You didn't just happen
to end up in my room

01:35.033 --> 01:36.601
a couple of times a day
for no reason.

01:36.601 --> 01:37.934
You know, you really--

01:37.934 --> 01:40.100
And you wouldn't be freaking out
about this so much

01:40.100 --> 01:41.601
if you didn't think I was right.

01:41.601 --> 01:42.901
That is not the point.

01:42.901 --> 01:44.067
So, what is the point?

01:44.067 --> 01:45.801
The-- The point is,
is that it-- It--

01:45.801 --> 01:47.968
Look, it is not gonna happen

01:47.968 --> 01:49.300
if I don't want it to happen.

01:50.534 --> 01:52.601
And I don't want it to happen.

01:58.334 --> 02:00.834
I got you this.

02:00.834 --> 02:02.300
Bailey.

02:02.300 --> 02:03.667
Oh, my God,
a kaleidoscope.

02:03.667 --> 02:04.667
I love these.

02:04.667 --> 02:05.667
Good.

02:05.667 --> 02:06.968
Oh, it's really beautiful.

02:06.968 --> 02:08.434
Where did you get this?

02:08.434 --> 02:10.934
Art museum. Yesterday.

02:10.934 --> 02:12.234
I would have gone with you.

02:12.234 --> 02:13.434
You should have called me.

02:13.434 --> 02:15.968
I would have,
but Callie needed to talk.

02:15.968 --> 02:17.968
And, you know, it's kind of
peaceful there.

02:17.968 --> 02:19.267
[DOOR OPENS]

02:19.267 --> 02:20.767
Hey, guys.

02:20.767 --> 02:22.267
Hey.

02:22.267 --> 02:23.634
Oh, those are great, huh?

02:23.634 --> 02:24.834
Oh, shoot.

02:24.834 --> 02:26.534
I forgot to pay you back
from yesterday.

02:26.534 --> 02:28.167
Don't worry about it.

02:28.167 --> 02:29.434
I'm such a copycat.

02:29.434 --> 02:31.267
I saw yours, just had to have
one for me too.

02:32.601 --> 02:35.200
I'm gonna warm up leftover Thai.
You guys want?

02:35.200 --> 02:36.968
I could eat.

02:36.968 --> 02:38.334
Sarah, any for you?

02:38.334 --> 02:40.534
I found this great new place.

02:40.534 --> 02:41.601
No MSG.

02:41.601 --> 02:43.267
Oh, you know what?
I have-- I have to go.

02:43.267 --> 02:44.667
There's plenty.

02:44.667 --> 02:46.033
Yeah. Stay.

02:46.033 --> 02:47.434
Come on, don't do this.

02:47.434 --> 02:48.601
You know how my parents get.

02:48.601 --> 02:50.501
Right. You'll turn
into a pumpkin

02:50.501 --> 02:52.934
if you're not home by midnight.

02:52.934 --> 02:55.367
Oh, well, more for me, then.

02:56.801 --> 02:58.667
Come on, I'll walk you down.

03:01.234 --> 03:03.334
Sarah.

03:03.334 --> 03:04.601
Sarah, you coming?

03:06.234 --> 03:08.834
