03:42.000 --> 03:44.501
Has anybody seen my...?

03:44.501 --> 03:45.567
Give me that.

03:45.567 --> 03:47.033
I just spent
the last 20 minutes--

03:47.033 --> 03:48.567
That there boat.

03:48.567 --> 03:49.701
No. It's my shoe.

03:56.033 --> 03:57.100
You want this?

03:57.100 --> 03:58.634
Or I could make
you something else.

03:58.634 --> 03:59.634
What would you like?

03:59.634 --> 04:01.767
Nothing. I'm not hungry.

04:03.434 --> 04:04.434
Charlie.

04:04.434 --> 04:05.701
What?

04:05.701 --> 04:08.534
Nothing.

04:08.534 --> 04:10.133
You wanna go see
a movie tonight?

04:10.133 --> 04:13.234
We never do that, you and me.
Let's do that.

04:13.234 --> 04:15.467
There's nothing I want to see.

04:15.467 --> 04:16.868
There's gotta be.
What about--?

04:16.868 --> 04:20.267
I'm not feeling like it, okay?

04:20.267 --> 04:23.133
So who's the lucky winner that
gets to drop me at school?

04:23.133 --> 04:24.701
No. Take the bus
like everybody else.

04:25.734 --> 04:27.834
You light up my life too,
Charlie.

04:27.834 --> 04:28.801
Claudia.
What?

04:30.300 --> 04:31.534
He's been in a mood all week.

04:31.534 --> 04:33.834
Frankly, I'm getting a little
tired of having to--

04:33.834 --> 04:34.834
Claudia,

04:34.834 --> 04:36.701
look at the calendar.

04:36.701 --> 04:38.601
Why? Is Mercury in retrograde
or something?

04:38.601 --> 04:39.901
It's a year.

04:39.901 --> 04:42.133
A year tomorrow the wedding.

04:44.834 --> 04:47.167
Man, I-- I totally...

04:47.167 --> 04:50.667
This would have been their first
anniversary.

04:50.667 --> 04:53.734
And I bet we would have been
planning some big--

04:53.734 --> 04:54.934
Where are my damn keys?

04:54.934 --> 04:56.434
Uh, right there.

04:59.334 --> 05:00.267
Charlie?

05:01.801 --> 05:02.834
[SIGHS]

05:02.834 --> 05:05.534
Have-- Have
a good day at work.

05:05.534 --> 05:06.467
Okay?

05:11.334 --> 05:13.367
MAN:
Yo, Charlie, you here?

05:13.367 --> 05:15.167
Anybody home?

05:16.434 --> 05:18.801
Joe, hey.
Hey.

05:18.801 --> 05:19.801
You look great.

05:19.801 --> 05:21.267
Thanks.
How'd you--?

05:21.267 --> 05:22.767
Did I know you were gonna
be in town?

05:22.767 --> 05:24.834
No. I thought I'd spring
it on you. How you doing?

05:24.834 --> 05:27.534
I'm doing...

05:27.534 --> 05:28.968
I'm doing.
Great.

05:28.968 --> 05:31.167
Well, come here. There's
somebody I want you to meet.

05:32.534 --> 05:34.234
Joe. This isn't--
No. Come on. Come on.

05:34.234 --> 05:36.133
No. Seriously, listen,
I know you mean well,

05:36.133 --> 05:39.067
but I'm really
not in the mood.

05:39.067 --> 05:40.801
You think this is a fix-up?

05:40.801 --> 05:44.067
Hey, Franny, he thinks I'm
trying to fix you up with him.

05:44.067 --> 05:45.200
Why?

05:45.200 --> 05:46.767
Are you bored with me already?

05:46.767 --> 05:48.234
[BOTH LAUGH]

05:48.234 --> 05:50.100
Charlie Salinger,
Franny Steiner.

05:50.100 --> 05:52.334
Hey, I am so glad to meet you.

05:52.334 --> 05:54.501
Joe talks about you
and the other kids constantly.

05:54.501 --> 05:58.467
Yeah. I'm-- I'm glad too.

05:58.467 --> 06:01.367
It happened.

06:01.367 --> 06:02.634
I fell in love.

06:03.701 --> 06:04.634
You guys?

06:06.067 --> 06:07.868
[LAUGHS]

06:07.868 --> 06:09.601
Well, now I feel--

06:09.601 --> 06:11.734
Yeah, well, I'm surprised too.

06:11.734 --> 06:14.734
I mean, I wake up in the
morning, and I half expect God

06:14.734 --> 06:17.567
or somebody to come down
and tell me it's a joke,

06:17.567 --> 06:21.267
that this-- This woman...

06:23.100 --> 06:24.467
She wants to marry me.

06:24.467 --> 06:26.367
You're getting married?

06:26.367 --> 06:28.033
That's...

06:28.033 --> 06:29.634
Wow.

06:29.634 --> 06:30.834
When?

06:30.834 --> 06:32.334
You don't have anything
important 

06:32.334 --> 06:33.634
planned here on Sunday, do you?

06:33.634 --> 06:35.400
This Sunday?

06:39.968 --> 06:43.100
So, um, Callie, you seem better,

06:43.100 --> 06:44.734
since-- Since the thing,
you seem--

06:44.734 --> 06:46.167
Yeah. Yeah.

06:46.167 --> 06:47.667
Back on the planet, pretty much.

06:47.667 --> 06:49.367
You know, I'm sleeping better,

06:49.367 --> 06:51.167
getting out of the apartment,
doing stuff.

06:52.367 --> 06:53.534
With Bailey?
Yeah, some.

06:53.534 --> 06:55.701
You know, when he's right there.
Mm.

06:55.701 --> 06:57.801
Yeah.

06:57.801 --> 07:00.334
Oh, you know, actually, I was
thinking about what you said,

07:00.334 --> 07:02.434
um, about how there are
no nice guys out there.

07:02.434 --> 07:04.400
You know, and I know that what
you went through

07:04.400 --> 07:05.567
was was bad and all.
I do.

07:05.567 --> 07:07.200
But I think maybe
it's time for you to...

07:09.467 --> 07:11.567
Anyway, I want you
to meet my cousin.

07:11.567 --> 07:14.734
Okay? He's really cute.
Very nice. I could call him.

07:14.734 --> 07:16.200
You know what?
I'm gonna call him.

07:16.200 --> 07:17.701
Thank you. Thanks, but--

07:17.701 --> 07:19.400
I think you guys
could really get along.

07:19.400 --> 07:21.634
You know, I have a pretty good
idea of your type.

07:21.634 --> 07:22.868
Okay.

07:22.868 --> 07:24.167
Nonfat latte.

07:24.167 --> 07:26.234
Fat latte.

07:29.534 --> 07:30.801
Am I interrupting something?

07:30.801 --> 07:33.400
Sarah wants to fix me up.

07:33.400 --> 07:35.567
Why?

07:35.567 --> 07:36.567
What's wrong with you?

07:36.567 --> 07:38.200
On a blind date.

07:38.200 --> 07:39.801
You remember my cousin Paul.

07:39.801 --> 07:42.234
Come on, you remember him from
my dad's birthday party?

07:42.234 --> 07:43.434
Yes, you do.

07:43.434 --> 07:45.868
You guys talked about hockey.
You really liked him.

07:45.868 --> 07:47.167
Right, right, right, Paul.

07:47.167 --> 07:48.968
Right, well, I was
just saying that I think

07:48.968 --> 07:50.133
they would get along great.

07:50.133 --> 07:51.267
You think that's a good idea?

07:54.033 --> 07:56.434
Yeah. Yeah.

07:56.434 --> 07:58.234
Yeah, you know what, Cal?

07:58.234 --> 08:01.100
I think you should
go out with this guy.

08:01.100 --> 08:03.133
Okay.

08:03.133 --> 08:04.868
Okay. I'll do it.

08:04.868 --> 08:06.968
I'll go out with him
on one condition.

08:06.968 --> 08:08.567
Name it.

08:08.567 --> 08:09.968
You guys go too.

08:09.968 --> 08:12.133
What?
Yeah.

08:12.133 --> 08:14.534
We'll double.
It'll be less pressure that way.

08:15.868 --> 08:16.901
Oh, no.

08:16.901 --> 08:17.968
[LAUGHS]

08:17.968 --> 08:19.601
No, no, no.

08:19.601 --> 08:20.801
No.

08:20.801 --> 08:24.000
No. You two should get to know
each other, alone.

08:24.868 --> 08:25.934
Right, Bailey?

08:28.234 --> 08:29.501
She has a point.

08:43.734 --> 08:46.567
I'm just putting these...

08:50.400 --> 08:53.534
If you'd let the sink fill,
I can soak them.

08:55.000 --> 08:56.634
Did you cut your hand?

08:56.634 --> 08:58.334
It's nothing.
I'm just cleaning it out.

08:58.334 --> 09:00.901
Can I get you some disinfectant
or something?

09:00.901 --> 09:02.300
No. It's fine.
You don't have to.

09:02.300 --> 09:04.267
I've got Band-Aids
in-- In the bathroom here.

09:04.267 --> 09:08.067
No, don't.
Don't get me anything.

09:08.067 --> 09:10.634
I can't even get a Band-Aid
for your hand?

09:10.634 --> 09:13.701
Look, I told--

09:13.701 --> 09:16.968
It's fine.

09:16.968 --> 09:19.534
So if you choked, I couldn't
give you a Heimlich?

09:19.534 --> 09:21.000
I'm only trying to help.

09:21.000 --> 09:24.300
Look, could we not do this right
now if-- If you don't mind?

09:24.300 --> 09:28.033
So now it's we can't even
be friends?

09:28.033 --> 09:30.667
No, Julia, we can't.

09:34.133 --> 09:35.133
[SIGHS]

09:35.133 --> 09:36.434
CLAUDIA:
I think it's so great

09:36.434 --> 09:37.868
that you guys met on a plane.

09:37.868 --> 09:39.400
Yeah. Talk about
love is in the air.

09:39.400 --> 09:41.267
[BOTH LAUGH]
JOE: Oh, yeah, I'll tell you.

09:41.267 --> 09:42.667
It was a crazy flight.

09:42.667 --> 09:44.634
First, the movie broke
halfway through,

09:44.634 --> 09:46.734
and people were very rowdy
about that.

09:46.734 --> 09:47.901
And then some little kid,

09:47.901 --> 09:50.567
he locks himself
in the bathroom for two hours.

09:50.567 --> 09:52.801
And there was turbulence,
not a little,

09:52.801 --> 09:54.567
and we're bouncing
all over the place.

09:54.567 --> 09:56.267
And I'm handing Joey
some orange juice,

09:56.267 --> 09:57.834
and right then
the plane jolts.

09:57.834 --> 10:01.367
And everybody screams, and juice
goes flying everywhere.

10:01.367 --> 10:04.100
All over his pants, his shirt,
the book he's reading.

10:04.100 --> 10:06.200
I didn't know whether
to laugh or cry.

10:06.200 --> 10:08.667
But then I look at him,
and he's smiling at me

10:08.667 --> 10:10.334
just like he is right now.

10:10.334 --> 10:12.534
And I said, "What else is gonna
happen on this trip?"

10:12.534 --> 10:15.467
And he says, "Who knows?

10:15.467 --> 10:17.501
Maybe something wonderful."

10:17.501 --> 10:19.267
ALL:
Aw!

10:19.734 --> 10:20.767
[LAUGHS]

10:20.767 --> 10:21.767
Well, I think it's time

10:21.767 --> 10:24.234
for this guy
to go to bed, huh?

10:24.234 --> 10:25.300
Night, O.

10:25.300 --> 10:26.501
JULIA:
Say night, night.

10:26.501 --> 10:28.000
ALL:
Good night, Owen.

10:29.267 --> 10:30.534
Well, Franny,

10:30.534 --> 10:32.601
getting married ought to be
pretty easy for you.

10:32.601 --> 10:35.167
Seeing as you have all that
experience walking down aisles.

10:35.167 --> 10:36.167
[LAUGHS]
Oh, God.

10:36.167 --> 10:37.534
Right. And instead of rice,

10:37.534 --> 10:39.501
we can give people little
packets of peanuts.

10:39.501 --> 10:42.400
Would you guys please? I mean,
a little reverence.

10:42.400 --> 10:43.934
This is our wedding.

10:43.934 --> 10:45.200
CLAUDIA:
Yeah.

10:46.667 --> 10:47.934
This is like...

10:50.133 --> 10:53.100
This is the best thing that's
happened in a really long time.

10:56.133 --> 10:57.400
Yep.

10:57.400 --> 10:59.534
I'm gonna get a refill.

10:59.534 --> 11:02.234
Uh, Charlie, you want to show me
where you hide the decaf?

11:04.033 --> 11:05.367
[CLEARS THROAT]

11:06.067 --> 11:07.400
So?

11:07.400 --> 11:08.434
I'm getting it.

11:08.434 --> 11:09.901
No. I don't care
about the coffee.

11:09.901 --> 11:11.634
You barely spoke
two words all night.

11:13.634 --> 11:15.234
You know, Charlie, I, um--

11:15.234 --> 11:18.033
I heard a little bit about
what happened to Kirsten.

11:18.033 --> 11:20.400
Not much. Just what
the kids told me.

11:20.400 --> 11:22.601
I don't know if it's something
you wanna talk about.

11:22.601 --> 11:24.501
No.
Okay. Okay.

11:26.634 --> 11:28.000
So, what do you think of her?

11:29.934 --> 11:31.300
She's nice.

11:31.300 --> 11:35.701
I was hoping for a little more
enthusiasm from my best man.

11:35.701 --> 11:37.968
You-- You will be my best man,
won't you?

11:40.601 --> 11:42.534
If you want me to.

11:43.701 --> 11:44.968
But--
But?

11:44.968 --> 11:46.334
There's a "but"?

11:46.334 --> 11:48.200
Well, you don't--

11:48.200 --> 11:51.067
You haven't known her very long,
Joe.

11:51.067 --> 11:52.334
I mean, a month?

11:52.334 --> 11:56.367
Well, I know her long enough
to know I love her.

11:56.367 --> 11:59.133
What am I gonna accomplish
by waiting, Charlie?

11:59.133 --> 12:00.133
I'm 50 years old.

12:00.133 --> 12:02.133
Right.

12:02.133 --> 12:05.200
You're 50, and she's what?

12:05.200 --> 12:06.534
A little older than I am?

12:06.534 --> 12:08.701
Thirty? Maybe 31?
That's-- That's 20--

12:08.701 --> 12:09.734
I've known her a month.

12:09.734 --> 12:11.367
She's 30.
I'm 20 years older.

12:11.367 --> 12:12.801
What are you giving me
numbers for?

12:14.100 --> 12:16.634
Didn't you notice how much we
love each other?

12:16.634 --> 12:18.033
Hey, you asked me
and I told you--

12:18.033 --> 12:19.300
Why are you doing this?

12:19.300 --> 12:20.300
Doing what?

12:20.300 --> 12:22.601
You're being so-- I don't know.

12:22.601 --> 12:25.200
This doesn't feel like you,
Charlie. You're not even here.

12:25.200 --> 12:27.167
It's like you're completely
somewhere else.

12:27.167 --> 12:28.534
Oh, cut it out, Joe.

12:28.534 --> 12:31.467
What the hell's that mean,
I'm not even here? God.

12:31.467 --> 12:33.567
Look, I know this isn't
the easiest time for you,

12:33.567 --> 12:36.067
and I know that
you miss Kirsten.

12:36.067 --> 12:38.701
And I'm not gonna
take that away from you,

12:38.701 --> 12:42.334
but this, Franny and me,

12:42.334 --> 12:43.667
this is a good thing.

12:45.167 --> 12:47.801
You guys are my family,
and we need to celebrate this.

12:50.200 --> 12:52.400
So I'm gonna
go back in there.

12:52.400 --> 12:55.033
And you come when you're ready
to be happy for us.

13:06.734 --> 13:08.367
CHARLIE:
Is that new?

13:10.834 --> 13:12.133
Someone donated it.

13:12.133 --> 13:13.400
I'm doing labels.

13:13.400 --> 13:16.400
I hate labels.

13:16.400 --> 13:18.100
I put together this list.

13:18.100 --> 13:19.801
A bunch of restaurants
near Salinger's

13:19.801 --> 13:22.267
who might want to get
on the program.

13:22.267 --> 13:25.133
It's got the names and numbers
of people you need to talk to.

13:25.133 --> 13:27.334
Well, that's great, Charlie.

13:27.334 --> 13:30.000
I mean, you could have faxed it,
but really, thanks.

13:33.400 --> 13:34.868
So...
So?

13:37.467 --> 13:40.634
So, uh, are you free on Sunday?

13:40.634 --> 13:43.834
Why? You mean for us to get
together and do something?

13:43.834 --> 13:45.534
Uh, yeah.

13:45.534 --> 13:47.601
I don't think so.

13:47.601 --> 13:49.367
Damn. Why don't these things
ever stick?

13:49.367 --> 13:50.834
Come on, you didn't
even let me--

13:51.868 --> 13:53.100
There's this wedding.

13:53.100 --> 13:54.501
Oh, in that case,
definitely, no.

13:56.100 --> 13:58.868
You think people were teasing us
at that dance? That was nothing.

13:58.868 --> 14:01.167
You know what it's like to bring
somebody to a wedding?

14:01.167 --> 14:03.467
"Where'd you two meet?
How long have you been dating?"

14:03.467 --> 14:04.767
That definitely doesn't sound

14:04.767 --> 14:06.334
like a fun way to spend
an afternoon.

14:06.334 --> 14:09.801
Look, I went to the dance,
the charity thing,

14:09.801 --> 14:11.400
and you said you'd
return the favor.

14:11.400 --> 14:13.968
I distinctly remember
you saying that.

14:13.968 --> 14:16.601
So ask me to the next charity
thing you have to go to.

14:16.601 --> 14:18.701
Believe me, this would
definitely be considered

14:18.701 --> 14:19.901
an act of charity.

14:25.000 --> 14:27.367
You picked out
a wedding gift yet?

14:30.601 --> 14:33.000
Sam, is that--?

14:33.000 --> 14:34.334
Oh, hi.

14:34.334 --> 14:36.334
Hi.

14:36.334 --> 14:40.300
If you're looking for Sam,
he took over the Atkinson job.

14:40.300 --> 14:42.400
You're kidding?

14:42.400 --> 14:45.100
You-- You mean he's
not gonna finish?

14:45.100 --> 14:47.367
Well, don't worry about it.
We're just wrapping up.

14:49.367 --> 14:51.501
We'll be-- We'll be done
in a couple of days.

14:53.734 --> 14:56.033
Yeah. Hi.
I'm looking for Sam.

14:56.033 --> 14:58.400
Right. The Atkinson job.
Right.

14:58.400 --> 14:59.534
Yeah, I heard.

14:59.534 --> 15:01.300
Well, can--?
Can you leave him a message?

15:01.300 --> 15:03.234
Can you tell him
that Julia Salinger called

15:03.234 --> 15:07.467
of the Salinger job,
which he did not, like, finish.

15:07.467 --> 15:09.033
No, I--

15:09.033 --> 15:10.534
Can you just tell him
to call me?

15:10.534 --> 15:12.434
All right?

15:12.434 --> 15:14.167
Man, you got it bad.

15:14.167 --> 15:16.934
Claudia, do you mind? I'm having
a private conversation.

15:16.934 --> 15:19.968
Sharing your love troubles
with a roofer's assistant,

15:19.968 --> 15:21.400
how private is that?

15:21.400 --> 15:23.267
Look, just butt out, okay?

15:23.267 --> 15:24.601
This is weird.

15:24.601 --> 15:26.601
I mean, it's like
I'm embarrassed for you.

15:26.601 --> 15:30.200
You're chasing after some guy
who's not even interested.

15:30.200 --> 15:33.868
That's-- You know what?
This is none of your business.

15:33.868 --> 15:36.267
Oh, so you think maybe
if you're totally pathetic,

15:36.267 --> 15:37.400
he'll feel sorry for you?

15:37.400 --> 15:39.934
I mean, I know
I'm only 13 and all,

15:39.934 --> 15:41.200
but, you know, I'm pretty sure

15:41.200 --> 15:42.901
that doesn't make you
more attractive.

15:42.901 --> 15:45.868
Oh, really? Really?

15:45.868 --> 15:47.801
Well, if you have to know,
he kissed me.

15:47.801 --> 15:49.601
He kissed you?

15:49.601 --> 15:51.634
Yes.

15:51.634 --> 15:53.601
I kissed him,
and he kissed me back.

15:53.601 --> 15:56.067
He did.

15:56.067 --> 15:57.300
I didn't say a word.

15:57.300 --> 15:59.834
Look, you just obviously
don't get it.

15:59.834 --> 16:01.767
Oh, because I'm too young.

16:01.767 --> 16:02.934
Basically.

16:02.934 --> 16:05.734
Yeah, well,
at least I know it.

16:08.501 --> 16:10.200
No way. You are not.

16:10.200 --> 16:11.834
I am.
I'm going to.

16:11.834 --> 16:13.434
Spend an entire day
not talking?

16:13.434 --> 16:15.334
Yeah. I heard this piece
on the radio

16:15.334 --> 16:17.434
about these people who do this,
like, once a week.

16:17.434 --> 16:19.501
I mean, it really grounds them.

16:19.501 --> 16:21.667
You're not gonna start this
today, are you?

16:21.667 --> 16:23.267
[BOTH LAUGH]

16:23.267 --> 16:25.467
Look. Look at this.
I think they're getting along.

16:25.467 --> 16:27.968
I think they like each other.
This is good.

16:27.968 --> 16:30.767
How can you tell?
From the backs of their heads?

16:30.767 --> 16:31.968
I'm gonna go check.

16:31.968 --> 16:33.601
No, wait. Just let them--

16:33.601 --> 16:35.601
Well, you said we were gonna
double-date.

16:35.601 --> 16:37.501
I don't want to be rude.

16:39.334 --> 16:40.667
How are you guys doing?

16:40.667 --> 16:42.100
Okay.

16:42.100 --> 16:43.534
I'll race you to that tree.

16:44.634 --> 16:45.901
[YELPS]
[BOTH LAUGH]

16:45.901 --> 16:47.501
Watch it.

16:47.501 --> 16:49.000
So, what do you think?

16:49.000 --> 16:50.400
She's a babe.

16:50.400 --> 16:52.834
A little weird, but all those
cute points cancel it out.

16:53.901 --> 16:55.667
[LAUGHS]

16:55.667 --> 16:58.334
So any sparks?
Oh.

16:58.334 --> 17:00.968
Not unless someone's gonna light
a firecracker under him.

17:00.968 --> 17:01.934
[IMITATES SNORING]

17:03.868 --> 17:05.968
[LAUGHING]

17:08.901 --> 17:10.534
SARAH: Hey.
Hey.

17:10.534 --> 17:12.501
What's so funny?

17:12.501 --> 17:14.233
Nothing.

17:14.233 --> 17:15.901
Too dumb to explain.

17:17.867 --> 17:19.567
So, what do we know about them?

17:19.567 --> 17:22.032
Is she into arts and crafts?

17:22.032 --> 17:24.666
Indoor sports? Decorating?

17:24.666 --> 17:25.901
Who knows?

17:25.901 --> 17:27.400
Probably not even Joe.

17:27.400 --> 17:30.133
Barely known each other as long
as you and I have.

17:30.133 --> 17:33.534
Well, we know he likes cooking,
so how about--?

17:33.534 --> 17:35.100
Hey, bread maker.

17:35.100 --> 17:37.000
I've always wanted
one of these.

17:37.000 --> 17:38.133
You can have one of mine.

17:38.133 --> 17:41.133
I've got five of them
in my closet.

17:41.133 --> 17:43.801
So why are we here?
We should shop in your closet.

17:46.300 --> 17:49.434
Oh, you could smile,
you know.

17:49.434 --> 17:51.367
Is this better?

17:51.367 --> 17:54.033
Man, what's gotten into you?

17:54.033 --> 17:55.234
You really want to know?

17:57.767 --> 18:01.467
Today would have been my first
anniversary with Kirsten.

18:01.467 --> 18:04.534
Oh, wow.

18:04.534 --> 18:07.968
And now you're the best man
at another guy's wedding.

18:07.968 --> 18:10.534
Wow.

18:10.534 --> 18:12.367
But, you know, um,
being with you,

18:12.367 --> 18:13.634
it really-- It really helps.

18:13.634 --> 18:16.868
I mean, it makes it easier.

18:16.868 --> 18:19.667
Well, I'm glad.

18:21.033 --> 18:23.100
Why not, um,
if you're free tonight,

18:23.100 --> 18:25.167
why not come
to the rehearsal?

18:25.167 --> 18:26.734
Me? To the rehearsal?

18:26.734 --> 18:28.267
It might be fun.

18:28.267 --> 18:31.434
We'll hang around, talk, maybe
go to a movie afterwards?

18:31.434 --> 18:32.534
Charlie, I don't know.

18:32.534 --> 18:34.067
Say yes. Come with me.

18:34.067 --> 18:36.367
I could use a good friend.

18:36.367 --> 18:37.467
And we'll have a good time.

18:37.467 --> 18:39.167
You're probably
the only chance I have

18:39.167 --> 18:41.067
of getting an actual smile
on my face.

18:41.067 --> 18:44.033
You know what? I--

18:44.033 --> 18:45.667
I-- I wish I could

18:45.667 --> 18:47.467
because someone should do that,

18:47.467 --> 18:48.934
hold your hand
and be your friend,

18:48.934 --> 18:50.934
but, um, it shouldn't
be me.

18:50.934 --> 18:52.868
Grace, it's really no big deal.

18:52.868 --> 18:54.834
Yeah, it is, Charlie.

18:54.834 --> 18:56.901
Just hanging around, maybe
that's easy for you,

18:56.901 --> 18:58.901
but it's hard...

19:00.567 --> 19:01.868
Look, I'll go to the wedding.

19:01.868 --> 19:03.000
I will because I promised.

19:03.000 --> 19:06.300
But, um, this thing tonight,
I-- I can't.

19:06.300 --> 19:07.234
I'm sorry.

19:09.133 --> 19:10.334
Okay.

19:10.334 --> 19:14.167
Franny and I, we're gonna stand
right here.

19:14.167 --> 19:17.133
No. We're gonna stand
right here.

19:17.133 --> 19:18.901
And, then, the rest
of the congregation,

19:18.901 --> 19:20.734
that's you, Jules,

19:20.734 --> 19:23.200
will stand right in the circle
right here.

19:23.200 --> 19:24.868
I'm in the circle.
I am the circle.

19:24.868 --> 19:26.267
And, Claudia.

19:26.267 --> 19:27.968
You're Charlie.

19:27.968 --> 19:31.200
So you come in with the rings,
which you better not forget.

19:31.200 --> 19:34.100
And then you go back and you
stand in the circle.

19:34.100 --> 19:36.267
And then we say
a couple of nice words,

19:36.267 --> 19:37.801
the best of which are "I do."

19:37.801 --> 19:39.801
And then I kiss
my beautiful bride.

19:39.801 --> 19:41.801
[GIGGLES]
Mwah.

19:41.801 --> 19:44.834
Then we dance and we sing
and we celebrate.

19:44.834 --> 19:45.868
Sorry I'm late.

19:45.868 --> 19:47.901
Oh, don't do this to us,
Charlie.

19:47.901 --> 19:49.167
My Joey has a heart condition.

19:49.167 --> 19:50.734
The last thing he needs
is suspense.

19:50.734 --> 19:53.300
See, that's one of the joys
of a May/December romance.

19:53.300 --> 19:54.667
She coddles me like a baby.

19:54.667 --> 19:56.200
What's a May/December romance?

19:56.200 --> 19:59.033
Oh, that's when one of you has
a few extra months on the other.

19:59.033 --> 20:00.801
Oh, you mean like
with Julia and Sam?

20:02.868 --> 20:04.000
Claudia.

20:04.000 --> 20:06.067
CHARLIE: Sam?
Who's Sam?

20:06.067 --> 20:08.267
Sam, the roofer guy?
You-- You and Sam are going out?

20:08.267 --> 20:09.868
No. I am really--

20:09.868 --> 20:12.400
Let me get this straight.
You're dating-- How old's he?

20:12.400 --> 20:15.067
He's not that old, Charlie.
What is he? As old as me?

20:15.067 --> 20:16.901
You're dating
a 26-year-old roofer?

20:16.901 --> 20:18.901
No.
Actually, he's a 24-year-old.

20:18.901 --> 20:20.501
How did this happen?
He come on to you?

20:20.501 --> 20:22.701
I don't think so.
CHARLIE: It's out of line.

20:22.701 --> 20:23.734
Doesn't sound like you.

20:23.734 --> 20:25.367
CLAUDIA:
Actually, she kissed him.

20:25.367 --> 20:26.634
Would everybody just shut up.

20:27.734 --> 20:29.033
JULIA:
Shut up.

20:29.033 --> 20:30.234
Because nothing is going on.

20:30.234 --> 20:31.667
I am not going out with anybody,

20:31.667 --> 20:34.334
and it-- It's none of anybody's
business anyway, okay?

20:43.834 --> 20:46.367
Oh, I think I twisted my ankle
this afternoon.

20:46.367 --> 20:47.868
Bad?
Uh-uh.

20:47.868 --> 20:49.067
No. We can still go out.

20:49.067 --> 20:50.834
So, what do you wanna do
tonight?

20:50.834 --> 20:52.567
I don't know.
What do you wanna do?

20:52.567 --> 20:55.067
We sound like that movie <i>Marty.</i>

20:55.067 --> 20:56.000
Did you ever see it?

20:57.467 --> 20:59.968
They keep asking each other
that, these two guys, you know,

20:59.968 --> 21:01.801
"So, what do you want do
tonight, Marty?"

21:01.801 --> 21:02.801
[LAUGHS]

21:02.801 --> 21:04.467
It's good.
We could rent it.

21:06.300 --> 21:07.601
Not in a movie mood.

21:07.601 --> 21:09.367
Oh, okay.

21:09.367 --> 21:10.300
Pillow fight?

21:11.367 --> 21:12.367
Huh?

21:12.367 --> 21:15.367
I was-- Never mind.

21:15.367 --> 21:17.033
You know what?

21:18.734 --> 21:20.133
I'm actually kind of tired.

21:20.133 --> 21:21.767
You know, from all the skating.

21:21.767 --> 21:25.801
And we're gonna see each other
tomorrow at-- At Joe's thing.

21:25.801 --> 21:29.100
So maybe we should
just bag tonight,

21:29.100 --> 21:30.567
and I'll go back
to the apartment.

21:30.567 --> 21:32.300
Don't.

21:32.300 --> 21:34.400
Why not?

21:34.400 --> 21:39.934
Well, um, because I-- I just
thought of something

21:39.934 --> 21:42.334
that we can do that we kind of
haven't done before.

21:44.601 --> 21:46.400
And if...

21:46.400 --> 21:49.100
I've-- I've been thinking
about this a lot.

21:51.501 --> 21:53.133
I wanna sleep with you.

21:53.133 --> 21:55.934
Make love with you.

21:56.701 --> 21:57.801
[SCOFFS]

21:57.801 --> 22:00.801
Sounds so stupid
when you say it like that.

22:00.801 --> 22:04.667
But I want us to.

22:04.667 --> 22:09.100
We haven't-- We haven't talked
about this in a while,

22:09.100 --> 22:12.601
you know, and--
And there was a reason--

22:12.601 --> 22:14.734
I know all that stuff that
happened with Julia.

22:14.734 --> 22:18.567
So you know,
we'll be extra careful.

22:19.834 --> 22:20.834
But--

22:20.834 --> 22:22.300
Bailey,

22:22.300 --> 22:24.567
I love you.

22:26.200 --> 22:27.934
[***]

22:31.868 --> 22:33.167
Why are we waiting?

22:35.267 --> 22:36.868
It's time.

22:51.300 --> 22:53.868
Look, you said you were tired.

22:53.868 --> 22:55.767
And-- And the wrestling,
that's probably--

22:55.767 --> 22:58.133
Look, can we--?

22:58.133 --> 23:00.000
Can we not talk about this,
please.

23:01.734 --> 23:03.067
Okay.

23:09.167 --> 23:10.534
Did I

23:11.801 --> 23:13.701
do something wrong?

23:14.801 --> 23:16.200
I mean, was I not...?

23:18.801 --> 23:20.334
Sorry.

23:20.334 --> 23:21.834
Um...

23:28.067 --> 23:29.968
I'm gonna--

23:29.968 --> 23:31.267
I'm gonna go.

23:35.701 --> 23:38.334
So, um,

23:38.334 --> 23:40.801
12:30 at the restaurant,
right?

23:43.267 --> 23:44.901
Twelve-thirty.

23:51.734 --> 23:53.000
It wasn't you.

23:59.334 --> 24:01.701
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

24:05.601 --> 24:08.767
The first time I met Joe,
I was just a kid in diapers.

24:08.767 --> 24:11.400
[SIGHS]
Snore, snore.

24:16.934 --> 24:19.300
You've gotta take your hat off
to anyone brave enough

24:19.300 --> 24:21.467
to believe in a thing
like getting married.

24:21.467 --> 24:23.067
[KNOCK AT DOOR]

24:24.033 --> 24:26.334
Charlie, hi.

24:27.100 --> 24:28.467
I just wanted to say--

24:28.467 --> 24:30.434
I mean, I know
you think we're such

24:30.434 --> 24:33.167
superstitious goofballs not
wanting to see each other

24:33.167 --> 24:34.501
before the wedding.

24:34.501 --> 24:35.968
No.
And, I mean,

24:35.968 --> 24:38.000
not only for letting me
stay here last night,

24:38.000 --> 24:41.534
but letting us
use the restaurant and...

24:41.534 --> 24:44.133
And being Joe's best man.

24:44.133 --> 24:46.567
I just wanted to say...

24:47.767 --> 24:48.767
Charlie?

24:49.968 --> 24:51.367
I'm sorry.

24:51.367 --> 24:52.501
[SIGHS]

24:52.501 --> 24:54.934
You just looked, um...

24:54.934 --> 24:57.834
You just--
That-- That dress.

24:57.834 --> 24:59.667
[LAUGHS]
Oh.

24:59.667 --> 25:01.868
Well, thanks.

25:01.868 --> 25:03.033
I mean, for that too.

25:03.033 --> 25:04.501
[CHUCKLES]

25:04.501 --> 25:06.167
So, um,

25:06.167 --> 25:07.534
thanks.

25:13.701 --> 25:15.100
[SIGHS]

25:21.033 --> 25:22.968
[***]

25:37.767 --> 25:40.000
Yeah, hi, um,

25:40.000 --> 25:42.734
I wanted to send some flowers
to someone in Chicago,

25:42.734 --> 25:45.067
uh, with, um, a note.

25:46.801 --> 25:48.767
[SIGHS]
Yeah.

25:48.767 --> 25:52.767
Uh, address it
to Kirsten Bennett.

25:52.767 --> 25:56.033
And I'd like it to say, um...

25:57.701 --> 26:00.734
You ready?

26:00.734 --> 26:03.200
Dear Kirsten,

26:03.200 --> 26:05.934
it's been a year and...

26:09.534 --> 26:12.634
I'm sorry,
let me start that again.

26:12.634 --> 26:13.701
[CLEARS THROAT]

26:13.701 --> 26:15.968
Kirsten, um...

26:17.734 --> 26:20.167
I just--

26:20.167 --> 26:21.701
I keep thinking about you,

26:21.701 --> 26:25.133
and I don't know what to say,

26:26.267 --> 26:30.200
or-- Or even whether
to say anything.

26:31.667 --> 26:33.734
Just that how much I always...

26:37.300 --> 26:39.067
You know what?
Maybe I should just--

26:39.067 --> 26:41.467
I should write this down
and call you back.

26:43.534 --> 26:44.601
Thanks.

26:55.734 --> 26:56.667
Hi.

26:58.434 --> 26:59.534
Oh, hey.

26:59.534 --> 27:01.000
Have you seen Bailey?

27:01.000 --> 27:02.067
He's not with you?

27:03.000 --> 27:04.701
Has he said anything to you

27:04.701 --> 27:05.868
recently about us?

27:05.868 --> 27:07.100
Nuh-uh.

27:08.067 --> 27:10.567
God, look at what I'm doing.

27:12.033 --> 27:14.300
You know,
something's wrong with us.

27:14.300 --> 27:16.267
Something's weird
and we both keep acting

27:16.267 --> 27:18.767
like it's the same,
but it's not.

27:18.767 --> 27:21.400
You know, and I keep trying to,
like, rewind the tape in my head

27:21.400 --> 27:23.234
and figure out
where it went bad.

27:24.133 --> 27:25.534
I don't know what to tell you.

27:25.534 --> 27:27.367
Can you ask him, maybe?

27:27.367 --> 27:30.100
Sarah, I can't do that.

27:31.400 --> 27:33.300
You're right.

27:34.667 --> 27:37.267
[SIGHS]
I'm, um, sorry.

27:47.901 --> 27:51.100
"What can you say about Joe
except here's a guy that's..."

27:51.100 --> 27:52.234
Hey.
Hey.

27:52.234 --> 27:53.400
Performance anxiety.

27:54.200 --> 27:55.467
Tell me about it.

27:57.234 --> 27:58.300
[SIGHS]

27:58.300 --> 27:59.400
Hey, Char,

27:59.400 --> 28:02.400
could you ever not...?

28:02.400 --> 28:04.501
Not what?
What are you doing with that?

28:04.501 --> 28:05.801
Give me a break, will you?

28:05.801 --> 28:07.334
I'm asking you something.

28:09.434 --> 28:11.868
With a woman, did you ever
not be able to--?

28:11.868 --> 28:13.667
Bailey.
No. No, I'm sorry.

28:13.667 --> 28:16.367
Of course not. Of course that
would never happen to you.

28:17.734 --> 28:21.334
But hypothetically if it--
If it happens,

28:21.334 --> 28:24.067
or if it doesn't happen--
Bay, I-- Not now, okay?

28:24.067 --> 28:25.434
JOE:
Bailey, Charlie,

28:25.434 --> 28:26.501
come on, you guys,

28:26.501 --> 28:28.234
let's get this show
on the road.

28:31.367 --> 28:33.667
Ladies and gentlemen,

28:33.667 --> 28:36.267
friends and family,

28:36.267 --> 28:39.467
a wedding like this
has witnesses,

28:39.467 --> 28:43.133
not only to support
the vows of Joseph and Francis,

28:43.133 --> 28:45.834
but also to strengthen the vows

28:45.834 --> 28:47.434
among the rest of us.

28:47.434 --> 28:49.534
They promise...
[WHISPERS] I'm sorry I'm late.

28:49.534 --> 28:51.701
How are you doing?

28:51.701 --> 28:53.167
Not great.

28:53.167 --> 28:54.701
I'm glad you're here, though.

28:57.367 --> 28:59.267
Oh, I'd better--

29:03.734 --> 29:06.734
Now, Francis, Joseph,

29:06.734 --> 29:09.434
if you'll repeat after me
a few simple words

29:09.434 --> 29:11.567
which signify your
commitment to each other...

29:11.567 --> 29:15.367
When I was a kid, he was just
Uncle Joe, you know,

29:15.367 --> 29:18.734
nobody special, just a guy
that worked with my dad.

29:18.734 --> 29:22.300
I, Joseph, ask you, Francis,

29:22.300 --> 29:25.734
to be my wife for as long
as we both live.

29:25.734 --> 29:27.868
But now he's--
He's actually the closest thing

29:27.868 --> 29:30.734
in the world
I have to a father.

29:30.734 --> 29:33.968
I will love you, honor you,
and stand by you always.

29:33.968 --> 29:36.667
I, Francis, ask you, Joseph,

29:36.667 --> 29:39.634
to be my husband for as long
as we both live.

29:39.634 --> 29:40.767
I, Francis,

29:40.767 --> 29:43.267
ask you, Joseph,
to be my husband

29:43.267 --> 29:45.300
for as long
as we both shall live.

29:45.300 --> 29:49.300
I will love you, honor you,
and stand by you always.

29:49.300 --> 29:50.634
I will love you,

29:50.634 --> 29:53.734
honor you,
and stand by you always.

29:53.734 --> 29:57.033
And now it's my pleasure
to pronounce you

29:57.033 --> 29:58.834
husband and wife.

29:58.834 --> 30:00.868
Joseph, you may kiss your bride.

30:04.834 --> 30:07.367
[APPLAUSE]
[CAMERA CLICKS]

30:14.801 --> 30:18.367
* You must remember this *

30:18.367 --> 30:21.267
* A kiss is still a kiss *

30:21.267 --> 30:24.834
* A sigh is just a sigh *

30:26.801 --> 30:30.801
* The fundamental things apply *

30:30.801 --> 30:33.934
* As time goes by *

30:34.934 --> 30:36.767
[CHUCKLES]

30:36.767 --> 30:38.067
Can I cut in, please?

30:38.067 --> 30:40.334
Oh, sure.

30:40.334 --> 30:41.934
Mwah.

30:41.934 --> 30:44.133
Hi.
Hey.

30:44.133 --> 30:45.801
Whoa.
[GIGGLES]

30:46.801 --> 30:47.868
Great.

30:50.200 --> 30:54.334
I'm, uh, sorry
I ruined your rehearsal.

30:54.334 --> 30:56.234
I-- I mean it.
I know. Don't worry about it.

30:56.234 --> 30:58.701
I just-- I don't--
I don't want you thinking

30:58.701 --> 31:01.367
that-- That last night
was because of you.

31:01.367 --> 31:04.601
It was just,
seeing you and Franny,

31:04.601 --> 31:06.601
it made me realize that

31:06.601 --> 31:09.133
people's ages shouldn't
have to matter, you know?

31:09.133 --> 31:13.067
And whatever Sam's reason is
for losing interest,

31:13.067 --> 31:16.067
it just had to be...

31:16.067 --> 31:18.834
well, something else.

31:21.968 --> 31:24.534
* It's still
The same old story *

31:24.534 --> 31:27.267
* A fight for love and glory *

31:27.267 --> 31:30.667
* A case of do or die *

31:32.901 --> 31:34.968
* The world will always *

31:34.968 --> 31:37.300
* Welcome lovers *

31:37.300 --> 31:40.334
Charlie, um, don't you
need to make a toast?

31:40.334 --> 31:42.367
Yeah, I do.

31:50.601 --> 31:52.734
Why are you being like this?

31:52.734 --> 31:53.868
Like what?

31:53.868 --> 31:56.367
You're hardly looking at me.

31:56.367 --> 31:58.834
And you're holding me like you
don't even want to touch me.

31:58.834 --> 32:01.801
Look, can we--? Can we please
not analyze this to death?

32:03.434 --> 32:05.834
It's hard enough we had to live
through it once without--

32:05.834 --> 32:07.000
[CLINKING GLASS]

32:08.300 --> 32:09.901
Can I get everybody's attention?

32:10.934 --> 32:12.000
Can I get everybody's--?

32:12.000 --> 32:13.167
[CHARLIE CLEARS THROAT]

32:13.167 --> 32:15.033
Um, I just have a few words.

32:17.968 --> 32:20.067
Thank you.
[SIGHS]

32:22.033 --> 32:23.801
What can you say
about Joe,

32:23.801 --> 32:27.133
except here's a guy
who leans hard on his luck?

32:28.934 --> 32:31.934
He, uh-- He let his partner's
kid take over his restaurant

32:31.934 --> 32:33.300
when all he knew about me was--

32:33.300 --> 32:35.801
Well, better left unsaid.

32:35.801 --> 32:36.834
[ALL LAUGH]

32:36.834 --> 32:39.133
So when he said he was
getting married

32:39.133 --> 32:41.434
to a woman he'd only known
for five weeks,

32:41.434 --> 32:43.334
and he wanted me to
stand up for him,

32:43.334 --> 32:47.067
I thought, man,
how long can his luck hold out?

32:48.467 --> 32:49.868
But then I realized that

32:49.868 --> 32:52.100
with something like this,
getting married,

32:52.100 --> 32:54.567
you know,
going the distance,

32:54.567 --> 32:57.000
luck is just the beginning.

32:57.000 --> 32:58.367
I mean, we're not here today

32:58.367 --> 33:00.567
because Joe was lucky enough
to find someone great.

33:00.567 --> 33:02.868
We're here because
he was smart enough

33:02.868 --> 33:04.567
not to let her go.

33:05.567 --> 33:06.968
There's always gonna be reasons

33:06.968 --> 33:08.868
to throw in the towel,

33:08.868 --> 33:12.267
but the people like Joe
who find love and don't lose it

33:12.267 --> 33:15.334
are the ones who just
hang in no matter what.

33:15.334 --> 33:18.567
Let's face it, how many times
are you gonna be that lucky?

33:18.567 --> 33:19.601
[CHUCKLES]

33:19.601 --> 33:22.734
Right person, right place,

33:22.734 --> 33:24.367
and you're actually ready?

33:26.501 --> 33:28.467
If that happens,
the biggest risk you can take

33:28.467 --> 33:30.100
is not taking a risk.

33:31.834 --> 33:34.267
I mean, something like
that doesn't...

33:40.267 --> 33:42.234
I'm sorry.

33:42.234 --> 33:43.334
[CHARLIE CLEARS THROAT]

33:50.200 --> 33:51.667
Joe, Franny.

33:51.667 --> 33:54.067
WOMAN: Joe and Franny.
ALL: Hear, hear.

33:54.067 --> 33:56.000
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

34:06.000 --> 34:07.934
[***]

34:27.266 --> 34:30.132
What are you doing here?

34:30.132 --> 34:32.167
And what are you wearing?

34:33.100 --> 34:35.333
Oh, I was at a wedding,

34:35.333 --> 34:37.000
but, um, I had
something to say

34:37.000 --> 34:39.067
so I kind of left
in the middle of it.

34:39.067 --> 34:40.967
Okay.

34:40.967 --> 34:44.167
I-- I don't-- I don't know
how you did it,

34:44.167 --> 34:48.333
but-- But somehow you made me
feel really stupid and pathetic.

34:48.333 --> 34:51.467
A-a-and that just seems
really wrong.

34:51.467 --> 34:53.234
I mean, hurt and-- And sad,
I understand.

34:53.234 --> 34:55.167
But-- But stupid and pathetic?

34:55.167 --> 34:58.434
What did I do?
I-- I-- I just said how I felt.

34:58.434 --> 35:01.968
You see, stupid to me
is what you are when, um--

35:01.968 --> 35:04.667
When you see what you want
but you let it-- Damn.

35:04.667 --> 35:07.567
And you just let it go.

35:07.567 --> 35:09.267
And-- And pathetic, I mean,

35:09.267 --> 35:12.367
what is more pathetic than
having to hide your emotions?

35:12.367 --> 35:15.634
You see, I'm 17 so I don't
have to play the--

35:15.634 --> 35:17.934
I don't have to play
the kind of game where--

35:17.934 --> 35:19.868
[TEARING]
The kind of game where--

35:19.868 --> 35:22.734
When-- When someone gets to you,
you just...

35:22.734 --> 35:24.234
You-- You wanna help me here?

35:26.234 --> 35:29.501
When someone gets to you, you--
You just shut off your emotions.

35:29.501 --> 35:32.334
You know, maybe when I'm 24,
I'll be all mature

35:32.334 --> 35:35.133
and in control and--
Watch the satin.

35:35.133 --> 35:38.434
And-- And I'll
play those games too.

35:38.434 --> 35:40.400
[FABRIC RIPS]

35:40.400 --> 35:41.968
[SIGHS]

35:41.968 --> 35:43.167
But I sure, uh--

35:44.334 --> 35:46.434
But I-- I sure hope I don't.

35:47.734 --> 35:49.400
You come all the way here
to tell me that?

35:50.234 --> 35:51.267
Yeah.

36:04.501 --> 36:05.501
Mm.

36:05.501 --> 36:06.567
Can I have your rose?

36:08.734 --> 36:09.734
Go for it.

36:09.734 --> 36:12.033
Thank you.

36:14.901 --> 36:16.267
Oh, hey.

36:17.234 --> 36:18.400
What are you doing that for?

36:18.400 --> 36:19.734
Oh, I'm, uh--

36:19.734 --> 36:21.534
I'm taking it home with me.

36:21.534 --> 36:23.501
There's some dumb tradition
that if you sleep

36:23.501 --> 36:25.767
with a piece of wedding cake
underneath your pillow,

36:25.767 --> 36:28.200
you'll see the person you're
gonna marry in your dreams.

36:28.200 --> 36:31.100
Ooh, I'm gonna try that.

36:33.968 --> 36:37.968
You know, I-- I had this
really bad audition once

36:37.968 --> 36:40.534
in the eighth grade
for <i>Pippin,</i>

36:40.534 --> 36:42.501
and I came home,
and I was all upset.

36:42.501 --> 36:45.901
You know, my mom said,
"So, what are you gonna do?"

36:45.901 --> 36:47.234
Why are you telling me this?

36:47.234 --> 36:50.467
Because just--

36:50.467 --> 36:52.100
Anyway, she said that.

36:52.100 --> 36:54.067
And I said, "Well, Mom,

36:54.067 --> 36:57.267
I'm gonna pretend
like it never happened."

36:57.267 --> 36:59.067
You know,
and she said, "Yeah.

36:59.067 --> 37:00.267
"Yeah, you can do that,

37:00.267 --> 37:02.300
"but I don't think
it's gonna work.

37:02.300 --> 37:06.000
"You know, I think what'll work
is if you go back the next time

37:06.000 --> 37:08.267
and you really give it
all you've got."

37:09.801 --> 37:11.734
[LAUGHS]

37:11.734 --> 37:14.601
God, she'd die if she knew
how I was using her advice.

37:19.100 --> 37:20.567
Look, I know
it was bad last night.

37:20.567 --> 37:23.801
Sarah--
I don't want to pressure you.

37:23.801 --> 37:25.868
And I know that there's
something wrong with us,

37:25.868 --> 37:28.033
but maybe that's why.

37:31.400 --> 37:34.367
But if we can...

37:34.367 --> 37:36.834
You know, if we can
do this right,

37:36.834 --> 37:38.133
then maybe what's wrong will--

37:38.133 --> 37:40.000
CLAUDIA:
Hey, Sarah. Sarah.

37:40.000 --> 37:42.767
Come on, Franny's getting ready
to throw the bouquet.

37:42.767 --> 37:45.133
All single women required.

37:47.434 --> 37:49.200
Can't we try again?

37:52.634 --> 37:54.067
Yeah,

37:54.067 --> 37:55.167
we can.

38:02.467 --> 38:05.033
Where have you been?

38:05.033 --> 38:06.367
Well, they're waiting for you.

38:06.367 --> 38:08.234
Franny wants
to throw the bouquet.

38:08.234 --> 38:10.534
They shouldn't have waited.

38:13.000 --> 38:15.000
Grace, I've been
looking for you.

38:17.701 --> 38:19.267
Where are you going?

38:19.267 --> 38:21.501
Home. I gotta go.

38:21.501 --> 38:23.300
No, don't go.

38:23.300 --> 38:25.000
Look, I--

38:25.000 --> 38:26.934
I feel like
I should apologize,

38:26.934 --> 38:28.901
because that...

38:28.901 --> 38:30.334
That toast--
Charlie, don't.

38:30.334 --> 38:31.734
It was great.

38:33.667 --> 38:36.100
Hey, don't run away.

38:36.100 --> 38:37.267
I gotta go.

38:37.267 --> 38:38.234
Why?

38:40.300 --> 38:42.701
Because this is too hard.

38:42.701 --> 38:45.834
But you were here,
and it was nice.

38:45.834 --> 38:47.200
I thought--
Well, it's not,

38:47.200 --> 38:49.534
because one minute
you're telling me

38:49.534 --> 38:51.133
you're waiting for her,
and the next,

38:51.133 --> 38:53.300
we're dancing and you're
pulling me really close.

38:53.300 --> 38:54.901
It was dancing.
That's all it was.

38:54.901 --> 38:57.267
And then you're giving this
beautiful toast about her,

38:57.267 --> 38:59.734
and then right after that
you're begging me to stay.

38:59.734 --> 39:02.434
And, Charlie,
I really can't do this.

39:05.434 --> 39:06.467
[SIGHS]

39:06.467 --> 39:07.734
I'm sorry.

39:07.734 --> 39:09.467
You're in some kind of limbo,

39:09.467 --> 39:10.901
and it's making you nuts.

39:12.367 --> 39:13.634
I don't know what to do.

39:14.868 --> 39:17.100
Well, then,
you gotta shake things up.

39:17.100 --> 39:19.400
If you're looking for answers,

39:19.400 --> 39:22.334
get moving, because you aren't
gonna find any here.

39:25.133 --> 39:26.968
I know there aren't any for me.

39:42.267 --> 39:43.434
SAM:
Did Lewis remember

39:43.434 --> 39:46.367
to do a second coat of paint
on that trim?

39:46.367 --> 39:48.234
Because if you don't
do a second coat,

39:48.234 --> 39:50.834
the first coat's
a waste of time.

39:52.601 --> 39:54.834
Oh, I'll just have to
come back tomorrow

39:54.834 --> 39:56.334
and check it
when the light's right.

39:57.534 --> 40:00.601
And if there's finish work
left to do,

40:00.601 --> 40:03.667
that Atkinson job
will just have to wait.

40:08.000 --> 40:10.267
You came all the way here
to tell me that?

40:16.367 --> 40:17.434
Yeah.

40:21.968 --> 40:24.734
Oh, now, Paul,
absolutely, definitely.

40:24.734 --> 40:26.133
I'll call you, okay?

40:26.133 --> 40:29.467
 <i>* I watch your ship crash</i>
 <i>On the rocks...*</i>

40:29.467 --> 40:32.634
You will not call him.

40:32.634 --> 40:36.567
You've got that when-pigs-fly
thing in your voice.

40:36.567 --> 40:37.701
[CHUCKLES]

40:37.701 --> 40:39.133
What?

40:39.133 --> 40:40.734
You mean I can't
lie to you anymore?

40:43.033 --> 40:44.334
Bummer, huh?

40:45.033 --> 40:45.968
You sharing?

40:46.934 --> 40:48.033
Mm.

40:49.100 --> 40:50.100
Mm.

40:51.200 --> 40:52.601
Souvenir from the wedding, huh?

40:52.601 --> 40:53.734
Yeah.
How was it?

40:55.133 --> 40:56.434
Pretty sappy.

40:59.934 --> 41:02.033
So, what's wrong with him?

41:03.234 --> 41:05.501
With Cousin Paul?

41:07.100 --> 41:09.234
I don't know.

41:09.234 --> 41:10.234
Nothing.

41:11.200 --> 41:12.367
He's fine.

41:15.000 --> 41:18.534
Except, you know how,
like, when you're with someone--

41:18.534 --> 41:20.434
And, I mean, even if
it's the first

41:20.434 --> 41:23.267
or second time you with them,

41:23.267 --> 41:26.834
and all of a sudden
you're thinking,

41:26.834 --> 41:29.734
I wonder what his skin
feels like,

41:29.734 --> 41:32.367
and you just--

41:32.367 --> 41:34.000
You want to touch him.

41:34.000 --> 41:36.067
You know?

41:36.067 --> 41:38.000
Or you want him to touch you.

41:41.834 --> 41:43.300
And I mean, if I'm--

41:43.300 --> 41:45.300
If I'm thinking that,

41:45.300 --> 41:47.501
then I know something good's
gonna happen.

41:49.033 --> 41:51.167
But if I don't think it...

41:51.167 --> 41:55.167
Like tonight, it didn't even
cross my mind once.

41:55.167 --> 41:57.467
The guy doesn't
stand a chance.

42:14.601 --> 42:15.667
[WHISPERS]
Cal.

42:20.701 --> 42:22.100
What?

42:31.234 --> 42:32.834
Are you sure?

42:33.901 --> 42:35.000
No.

42:39.467 --> 42:41.868
 <i>* I stand here naked *</i>

42:41.868 --> 42:44.901
 <i>* I have nothing left</i>
 <i>To conceal *</i>

42:46.234 --> 42:49.300
 <i>* Strange lovin' *</i>

42:51.000 --> 42:54.100
 <i>* They come and go *</i>

42:56.667 --> 42:59.534
 <i>* They come and go *</i>

42:59.534 --> 43:02.501
 <i>* And leave behind</i>
 <i>Rusted memories *</i>

43:02.501 --> 43:05.300
 <i>* And they come and go *</i>

43:05.300 --> 43:08.234
 <i>* Like secrets</i>
 <i>Between enemies *</i>

43:08.234 --> 43:10.501
 <i>* And they come and go *</i>

43:10.501 --> 43:13.834
 <i>* And sometimes</i>
 <i>It takes so long *</i>

43:13.834 --> 43:16.033
 <i>* That I just don't know *</i>

43:16.033 --> 43:17.667
Yes. Hi, uh,

43:17.667 --> 43:19.400
I wanted to know
about your flights

43:19.400 --> 43:21.501
from San Francisco to Chicago.

